article.headline: East Tenn. St. 98, Jacksonville 87
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- All five ETSU starters reached double-figure scoring as the Buccaneers beat Jacksonville 98-87 on Saturday. Senior Tim Smith lead ETSU (7-7, 4-3 Atlantic Sun) with 26 points, including his 2,000th career point. Travis Strong had a season-high 21 points and Brad Nuckles had 14 points and eight rebounds. Courtney Pigram and Andrew Reed both had 10 points. Antonio Cool 25 lead the Dolphins (1-13, 1-6) with 25 points, Evan Jefferson had a career-high 16 points and Marcus Allen had 14 points and nine rebounds. ETSU jumped out to a 17-point lead on a Nuckles free throw, making it 25-8 with 11:25 in first half. Jacksonville slowly chipped at the lead, cutting it to only four points at 43-39 going into halftime. The Buccaneers slowly pulled away during the second half.
